  <!-- Selection Criteria -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="selection-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Selection Guide</div>
      <h2 id="selection-heading" class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        How to Specify a Pallet Conveyor System
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          Pallet conveyor specification requires the following data points. Gather these before contacting manufacturers to ensure comparable RFQ responses.
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 ml-2">
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Pallet type and dimensions:</strong> GMA 48x40, Euro, custom? Stringer or block pallet? Wood, plastic, or steel?</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Maximum loaded weight:</strong> Heaviest pallet the system must handle, including the pallet itself.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Throughput:</strong> Pallets per hour in each direction. Consider peak rates, not just averages.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Layout:</strong> Straight runs, transfers (right-angle, 180-degree), elevation changes, and total system footprint.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Integration points:</strong> Palletizer model and discharge height, stretch wrapper type (turntable or rotary arm), pallet labeler position, dock door locations.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Accumulation:</strong> Number of staging positions before and after each machine. Buffer time requirements.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Environment:</strong> Indoor/outdoor, temperature (freezer, ambient, hot), washdown requirements for <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">food-grade applications</a>.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink">Controls:</strong> Standalone PLC, integration with existing plant controls, WMS interface, barcode/RFID tracking.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="apps-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="apps-heading" class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Pallet Conveyor Applications
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-2 mb-4">End-of-Line Packaging</h3>
        <p>
          The most common pallet conveyor application connects palletizer discharge to stretch wrapper to shipping dock. This end-of-line system automates the final steps of the <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging line</a>, replacing manual pallet jack transport with continuous automated flow. End-of-line pallet conveyors reduce labor requirements, improve throughput consistency, and eliminate pallet damage from forklift handling.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-8 mb-4">Warehouse Pallet Handling</h3>
        <p>
          Distribution centers use pallet conveyors to transport pallets between receiving docks, AS/RS systems, pick modules, and shipping staging. High-throughput DC operations handle hundreds of pallets per hour through conveyor networks that replace forklift traffic in critical aisles. Dematic, TGW, and Intelligrated provide fully automated pallet conveyor systems for these applications.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-8 mb-4">Empty Pallet Handling</h3>
        <p>
          Empty pallet dispensers and conveyors supply fresh pallets to palletizer infeed positions. Light-duty pallet conveyors transport empty pallet stacks from storage to dispensers. Pallet dispensers separate individual pallets from stacks and place them onto the palletizer infeed conveyor. Empty pallet systems also handle pallet return from depalletizing operations.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-8 mb-4">Food &#x26; Beverage Pallet Systems</h3>
        <p>
          <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Food and beverage plants</a> use pallet conveyors to move heavy loaded pallets of bottles, cans, cases, and bags. Beverage pallets often weigh 2,500-3,500 lbs, requiring heavy-duty CDLR conveyors. Food-grade pallet conveyor applications may require stainless steel frames and washdown-rated components in areas adjacent to processing zones. Arrowhead Systems (now Regal Rexnord Automation Solutions) specializes in pallet conveyor systems for food and beverage end-of-line applications.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  </article>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a pallet conveyor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A pallet conveyor is a heavy-duty material handling system that transports loaded or empty pallets through packaging, warehousing, and manufacturing operations. Pallet conveyors use <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">chain-driven live rollers (CDLR)</a>, drag chains, or heavy-duty powered rollers to move loads from 500 to 4,000+ pounds.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How much weight can a pallet conveyor handle?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Standard pallet conveyors handle 500-4,000 lbs. Light-duty conveyors carry empty pallets up to 1,000 lbs. Standard-duty handles typical GMA grocery pallets at 1,500-3,000 lbs. Heavy-duty configurations support 4,000+ lbs for beverages, drums, and industrial products. Load capacity depends on roller diameter, chain size, and frame construction.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the difference between CDLR and drag chain pallet conveyors?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p><strong class="text-ink">CDLR</strong> uses chain-driven steel rollers. Pallets ride on the rollers. CDLR supports accumulation through chain-to-roller slip. It is the most common pallet conveyor type.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-ink">Drag chain</strong> uses strands of chain running in tracks. Pallets ride directly on the chain. Drag chain handles heavier loads and non-standard pallet sizes but does not support accumulation without separate drive zones.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How do pallet conveyors integrate with stretch wrappers?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Turntable wrappers use chain transfers to move pallets on/off the turntable. Rotary arm wrappers keep the pallet on the conveyor while the wrapping arm rotates around it. The conveyor stages 2-3 pallets upstream of the wrapper to prevent the palletizer from stopping during the wrap cycle.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What speed do pallet conveyors run at?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Packaging line pallet conveyors run at <strong class="text-ink">20-60 FPM</strong>. Palletizer discharge runs 20-40 FPM. Transfer and staging conveyors run 30-60 FPM. Speeds above 60 FPM are possible but rarely needed for pallet handling. The speed must match the palletizer cycle time and downstream machine infeed rates.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
